  Kernel::OrientedSide_3  


A model for this must provide:
 

    
          Oriented_side   

         
          
             
    fo.operator() (     
      Kernel::Plane_3  h,  Kernel::Point_3  p)     
                
    returns   ON_ORIENTED_BOUNDARY  ,
  ON_NEGATIVE_SIDE  , or the constant   ON_POSITIVE_SIDE  ,
depending on the position of  p   relative to the oriented plane  h .
                 
          Oriented_side   

         
          
             
    fo.operator() (     
      Kernel::Tetrahedron_3  t,  Kernel::Point_3  p)     
                
    returns   ON_ORIENTED_BOUNDARY  ,
  ON_NEGATIVE_SIDE  , or the constant   ON_POSITIVE_SIDE  ,
depending on the position of  p   relative to the oriented tetrahedron  t .
                 
          Oriented_side   

         
          
             
    fo.operator() (     
      Kernel::Sphere_3  s,  Kernel::Point_3  p)     
                
    returns   ON_ORIENTED_BOUNDARY  ,
  ON_NEGATIVE_SIDE  , or the   ON_POSITIVE_SIDE  ,
depending on the position of  p   relative to the oriented sphere  s .
            

  Refines  AdaptableFunctor  (with two arguments)
 

  See Also   CGAL::Plane_3 &lt; Kernel &gt;    CGAL::Sphere_3 &lt; Kernel &gt;    CGAL::Tetrahedron_3 &lt; Kernel &gt;   

